import React from 'react'
import { Header, Icon, Image, Menu, Segment, Sidebar, Button, Grid } from 'semantic-ui-react'



class SidebarExampleSidebar extends React.Component {
  
  state = {
    visible: false
  }
  
  setVisible = (e) => {
    this.setState({ visible: !visible })
  }

  render() {
    return (
      <React.Fragment>
      <Sidebar.Pushable as={Segment}>
      <Sidebar
        as={Menu}
        animation='overlay'
        icon='labeled'
        inverted
        onHide={() => setVisible(false)}
        vertical
        visible={visible}
        width='thin'
      >
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='home' />
          Home
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='gamepad' />
          Games
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='camera' />
          Channels
        </Menu.Item>
      </Sidebar>

      <Sidebar.Pusher>
        <Segment basic>
          <Header as='h3'>Application Content</Header>
          <Grid>
            <Grid.Column width={6}></Grid.Column>
            <Grid.Column width={6}>
              <Button onClick={this.setVisible}>Click Me</Button>
            </Grid.Column>
          </Grid>u
        </Segment>
      </Sidebar.Pusher>
    </Sidebar.Pushable>
    </React.Fragment>
    );
  }
}

export default SidebarExampleSidebar
